you've got a boyfriend,

300
00:13:06,026 --> 00:13:09,994
you're pretty, you have
zero fashion sense, but...

301
00:13:09,996 --> 00:13:12,464
Anyway, tonight we're gonna do
whatever you want.

302
00:13:12,466 --> 00:13:13,498
Really?

303
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,767
Absolutely.
You name it, we're doing it.

304
00:13:16,569 --> 00:13:19,971
Basket weaving
at the craft museum.

305
00:13:19,973 --> 00:13:23,708
Well, you named it.

306
00:13:27,446 --> 00:13:29,280
Oh, here's another one.

307
00:13:29,282 --> 00:13:33,251
I wish that the apple pancake
mix was on the top shelf

308
00:13:33,253 --> 00:13:34,952
because it starts with an “A,”

309
00:13:34,954 --> 00:13:36,754
but I don't put it there

310
00:13:36,756 --> 00:13:38,956
because I don't want you
breaking one of your little legs

311
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:41,392
when you're supposed
to be making my breakfast.

312
00:13:42,695 --> 00:13:46,764
Is it my turn to talk
about the compromises I make?

313
00:13:46,766 --> 00:13:51,169
I wasn't done, but go ahead.

314
00:13:51,171 --> 00:13:54,839
He said, compromising.

315
00:13:54,841 --> 00:13:56,774
Because of you, I'm not allowed

316
00:13:56,776 --> 00:13:58,809
to adjust the temperature
in my own home.

317
00:13:58,811 --> 00:14:00,278
I'm not allowed to whistle.

318
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,580
I don't wear shoes
that might squeak.

319
00:14:02,582 --> 00:14:05,249
Well, you're a physicist,
not a circus clown.

320
00:14:05,251 --> 00:14:09,654
Sheldon, do you realize I don't
live with the woman I love

321
00:14:09,656 --> 00:14:11,288
because of you?

322
00:14:12,224 --> 00:14:13,624
No other reason. Just you.

323
00:14:13,626 --> 00:14:16,093
Is that true?
Yes, it's true. The last time

324
00:14:16,095 --> 00:14:17,495
I brought it up,
you had an emotional breakdown

325
00:14:17,497 --> 00:14:20,498
and got on a train and ran away.

326
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,266
Well, given my history
on the subject,

327
00:14:22,268 --> 00:14:25,136
it seems a little reckless
to bring it up now.

328
00:14:25,138 --> 00:14:29,440
You have no idea
how much you inconvenience

329
00:14:29,442 --> 00:14:31,075
the lives of everyone
around you.

330
00:14:31,077 --> 00:14:33,010
It's exhausting!

331
00:14:33,012 --> 00:14:34,478
You know what?

332
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,480
You think you're so tolerant,

333
00:14:36,482 --> 00:14:38,449
but the truth is...

334
00:14:38,451 --> 00:14:40,517
you're mean to me a lot.

335
00:14:40,519 --> 00:14:41,919
Yeah,
you think

336
00:14:41,921 --> 00:14:43,587
that I don't notice
all those sarcastic comments

337
00:14:43,589 --> 00:14:45,989
and those eye rolls,
but I do. Hmm?

338
00:14:45,991 --> 00:14:48,625
I have
excellent peripheral vision.

339
00:14:49,928 --> 00:14:53,864
On a good day,
I can see my ears.

340
00:14:54,866 --> 00:14:57,568
Sheldon, I-I'm sorry
if I hurt your feelings.

341
00:14:57,570 --> 00:15:00,370
I've been holding a lot
of this in for a while.

342
00:15:00,372 --> 00:15:02,039
Well, I'm sorry, too.
And if you want

343
00:15:02,041 --> 00:15:04,708
to live with Penny,
then I think you should.

344
00:15:04,710 --> 00:15:06,143
Do you mean that?

345
00:15:06,145 --> 00:15:08,512
Yes. Yeah, just put
on your squeaky shoes and...

346
00:15:08,514 --> 00:15:11,181
your way out of my life.

347
00:15:13,818 --> 00:15:15,819
